Form990ScheduleFPartIV.Identifier: PROCEDURES FOR MONITORING THE USE OF GRANT FUNDS OUTSIDE THE UNITED STATES
Form990ScheduleFPartIV.Explanation: Procedures for in country food aid and out of country food aid are the same as follows: 1. FMSC Pre-screens the requesting distribution partner before approval is given to receive FMSC product. Extensive correspondence over the type of feeding programs (school, church, village outreach, etc) and methods of distribution (served cooked, given out uncooked, etc), is completed as a part of this pre-screening process. 2. Approved Distribution Partners submit "project forms" prior to sending a container of food to a new feeding program, explaining the location of distribution, demographics, method of distribution, other outreach involved, etc. 3. All Distribution Partners are required to send FMSC a Receipt of Shipment that the container arrived as scheduled, as well as submit feedback to FMSC in the form of pictures, stories, and/or reports about the impact of the food once the distribution is underway. FMSC annually assesses Distribution Partner's performance. 4. If food is sent to a domestic warehouse prior to being shipped internationally, all the above applies just the same; these practices are still in place in-country.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: PROCESS THE ORGANIZATION USES TO REVIEW FORM 990.
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: A COPY OF FORM 990 IS INTERNALLY REVIEWED BY THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND THE DIRECTOR OF ADMINISTRATION AND FINANCE. IT IS THEN REVIEWED BY THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS BEFORE IT IS PRESENTED TO THE ENTIRE BOARD FOR FINAL APPROVAL. IF THE FULL BOARD IS NOT ABLE TO REVIEW THE 990 BEFORE FILING THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE HOLDS FINAL REVIEW.

IN CONNECTION WITH ANY ACTUAL OR POSSIBLE CONFLICTS OF INTEREST, AN INTERESTED PERSON (AS DEFINED IN THE POLICY) MUST DISCLOSE THE EXISTENCE OF HIS OR HER FINANCIAL INTEREST AND BE GIVEN THE OPPORTUNITY TO DISCLOSE ALL MATERIAL FACTS RELATING TO HIS OR HER FINANCIAL INTEREST TO THE DIRECTORS OR MEMBERS OF COMMITTEES WITH BOARD-DELEGATED POWERS CONSIDERING THE PROPOSED TRANSACTION OR ARRANGEMENT.

ANNUALLY A MEMBER OF THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD REVIEWS CURRENT COMPENSATION OF THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND KEY EMPLOYEES. USING INFORMATION GATHERED FROM PUBLIC SOURCES, THE COMMITTEE MEMBER DETERMINES WHAT THE MARKET STANDARD PAY IS IN THE 50% BRACKET OF COMPARABLE POSITIONS. THE EMPLOYEES ARE GIVEN PERFORMANCE APPRAISALS, AND THE CURRENT LEVEL OF PAY, EMPLOYEE PERFORMANCE, AND MARKET STANDARDS IS REVIEWED BY THE MEMBER OF THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE. THIS PERSON THEN RECOMMENDS AN INCREASE (IF MERITED) TO THE ENTIRE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE, WHICH APPROVES, DISAPPROVES OR RECOMMENDS A DIFFERENT WAGE.

GeneralExplanation.Explanation: COPIES OF ALL INFORMATION ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST. FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE MADE AVAILABLE THROUGH GUIDESTAR AND CHARITY REVIEW COUNCIL.

FEED MY STARVING CHILDREN IS A NON-PROFIT CHRISTIAN ORGANIZATION COMMITTED TO FEEDING GOD'S STARVING CHILDREN HUNGRY IN BODY AND SPIRIT. THE APPROACH IS SIMPLE: CHILDREN AND ADULTS HAND-PACK MEALS FORMULATED SPECIALLY FOR STARVING CHILDREN. WE PROVIDE A TEAM-BUILDING ENVIRONMENT WHERE PEOPLE OF ALL AGES CAN COME TOGETHER FOR A COMMON CAUSE: PACKING NUTRITIOUS, LIFE-SAVING MEALS FOR STARVING CHILDREN. WE THEN SHIP THE MEALS TO MORE THAN 60 COUNTRIES AROUND THE WORLD. WE CURRENTLY HAVE FOUR PERMANENT SITES: COON RAPIDS, EAGAN, AND CHANHASSEN MINNESOTA AND AURORA, ILLINOIS. FEED MY STARVING CHILDREN'S FOOD FORMULA IS DESIGNED TO MEET THE NEEDS OF SEVERELY MALNOURISHED CHILDREN. VOLUNTEERS PACK OUR FOOD AND CONTRIBUTE TO OUR MISSION ALL OVER THE UNITED STATES, WITH Mobile PACKING EVENTS OCCURRING THROUGHOUT THE YEAR. -MEAL PRODUCTION: 96,892,920 MEALS PRODUCED IN 2009-2010 -MEAL SHIPMENT: 94,413,624 MEALS SHIPPED IN 2009-2010 -VOLUNTEERS: 416,779 VOLUNTEERS IN 2009-2010
DURING FISCAL YEAR 2009, FMSC RECEIVED A DONATED VEHICLE. FMSC IS NOT REQUIRED TO FILE FORM 1098-C UNTIL 12/31/2010.
